type: web_research
title: US Options Trading Automation System - Deep Research Round 2
key_insights[15]: "Event-driven architecture with 4 components: Producers, Consumers, Channels, Processors - ideal for trading systems","NautilusTrader uses DDD + event-driven + crash-only design, Python/Rust hybrid, single-threaded kernel for determinism","ThetaGang is production-proven IBKR wheel strategy bot with VIX hedging, regime-aware rebalancing, TOML config","TradingAgents v0.2.0 (Feb 2026): 7-role multi-agent LLM framework supporting Claude 4.x, GPT-5.x, Gemini 3.x","Alpaca MCP Server: 43+ endpoints for stocks/ETFs/crypto/options, integrates directly with Claude Desktop","FastStream: unified async Python framework for Kafka/RabbitMQ/NATS/Redis event streaming",FinBERT + LSTM combination shown most effective for financial sentiment-based price prediction,"Polygon.io (now Massive.com): full OPRA feed, real-time Greeks, IV, options chain snapshots via REST/WebSocket","tastytrade SDK: typed async Python SDK with DXLink websocket streaming for real-time quotes and Greeks","QuantConnect LEAN: seamless backtest-to-live with same code, supports options, Python 3.11","Risk management essentials: Kelly Criterion, Fixed Fractional, Volatility Targeting for position sizing","Circuit breakers: 3% daily loss pause, 10% drawdown halt, consecutive loss detection","Earnings strategy: short ATM straddles, delta-neutral, short vega for IV crush capture","Greeks libraries: QuantLib (industry-grade), py_vollib (fast), mibian (simple BS model)","Unusual options activity: volume/OI ratio > 5x average signals institutional interest"
refs[9]: "NautilusTrader architecture: nautilustrader.io/docs/latest/concepts/architecture/","ThetaGang: github.com/brndnmtthws/thetagang","TradingAgents: github.com/TauricResearch/TradingAgents","Alpaca MCP: github.com/alpacahq/alpaca-mcp-server","FastStream: github.com/ag2ai/faststream","FinBERT: github.com/ProsusAI/finBERT","Polygon.io Options: polygon.io/options","tastytrade SDK: github.com/tastyware/tastytrade","QuantConnect LEAN: github.com/QuantConnect/Lean"
recommendations[8]: Use NautilusTrader as execution backbone for high-performance options trading,Integrate TradingAgents for multi-agent LLM analysis with Claude 4.x as deep thinker,Deploy Alpaca MCP Server for Claude Code direct integration and paper trading,"Use FastStream + Redis for real-time data pipeline, Kafka for persistence",Implement FinBERT + custom LLM pipeline for sentiment analysis,"Use QuantConnect LEAN for backtesting, NautilusTrader for live execution",Adopt event-driven microservice architecture with message bus,"Implement 3-tier risk: pre-trade validation, real-time monitoring, circuit breakers"
